    "Page 14 TheHews Girt light and the people will find their own wag A ScrippsHoward Newspaper By Carrier Week 10c By Mail Month 60c Year S7JO 1013 13th St N W Phone District 7777 LOWELL MELLETT NELSON P POYNTER Editor Business Manager GRASS ROOTS PRINCIPLES JEPUBLICANS in their declaration of principles at their Grass Roots convention reaffirmed state sovereignty They then proceeded to declare for 1 A living wage and a saving wage 2 the full dinner pail 3 national recognition for agriculture with a fair and proportionate part of the national income for the farmer 4 economic fraternalism between farm workers and indus try 5 equality of economic opportunity for all men 6 abolishment of child labor in industry 7 regulation of em ployment of women in industry in the interest of their health and welfare Just how all those things can be attained with every state acting as it pleases is not explained in the declaration And that is the question It is the question that promises to dominate the campaign of 1936 and other campaigns if necessary until it is settled Child labor for example How in a competitive system can industries survive in states that have"
